      <blockquote> 
        <h2 align="left">Simulation Creation Control Panel</font></h2>
        <p align="left">Now that he has reached the Simulation Creation Control 
          Panel (shown below), Mike H. will work his way down the steps shown 
          in gold listed on the left. Please note the following items on this 
          page:</p>
      </blockquote>
      <ul>
        <li>The Steps shown in gold underlined letters (hyperlinks) running down 
          the left hand side of the screen are intended to be accessed more or 
          less sequentially. These are the steps one will go through in creating 
          a simulation.</li>
        <li>In the right hand panel one can see context dependent help. </li>
        <li>Clicking on a white hyperlink will show help on the item selected 
          in the right hand panel. (Gold hyperlinks are what one clicks on to 
          navigate normally around the web application.)</li>
        <li>In the upper right hand corner of the main screen, one can see links 
          to the major 4 application sections (Think, Create, Play and Share).</li>
        <li>In the lower left hand corner of the main screen, one can logout or 
          go back to the Introduction Page.</li>
        <li>In the lower right hand corner of the main screen, one access one's 
          own profile. Your profile contains important information, such as your 
          email address. This will be used when sending out emails to the players 
          informing them that a simulation has begun.</li>
      </ul>
